<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="283 - 329" refId="B266" refString="Ohaus, F, 1905. Beitraege zur Kenntniss der amerikanischen Ruteliden. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 66: 283 - 329" title="Beitraege zur Kenntniss der amerikanischen Ruteliden." volume="66" year="1905">Ohaus (1905)</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ludovici" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludovici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ludovici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The holotype specimen was collected on the flowers of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“mimosa”">&quot;mimosa&quot;</normalizedToken>
. The species was described based on a single male specimen that was collected by his brother in the state of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo on the bank of the Rio Doce between Baixo Guandu and Timbuhy (collecting date Dec. 21, 1898) (
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="283 - 329" refId="B266" refString="Ohaus, F, 1905. Beitraege zur Kenntniss der amerikanischen Ruteliden. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 66: 283 - 329" title="Beitraege zur Kenntniss der amerikanischen Ruteliden." volume="66" year="1905">Ohaus 1905</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pelidnota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pelidnota ludovici" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludovici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pelidnota ludovici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a metallic green morphotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We considered that the holotype may represent a teneral specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we examined two specimens both from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo (probably representing different collecting events). The ventral surface is metallic rufous with metallic green shine in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ludovici" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludovici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ludovici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(black with metallic green in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); legs are metallic rufous or purple (black in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); head is shiny, metallic green (also in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum, scutellum, and elytra are metallic rufous with green shine (pronotum and scutellum metallic green, elytra black and shiny in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmeisteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Based on comparison of types of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ludovici" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludovici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ludovici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. burmeisteri subsp. tricolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="burmeisteri" subSpecies="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. burmeisteri tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(male genitalia and other characters), we consider these taxa to be conspecific. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohaus" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pelidnota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pelidnota ludovici" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludovici">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pelidnota ludovici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ohaus is a 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">new synonym</emphasis>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nonfried" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pelidnota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pelidnota burmeisteri subsp. tricolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="burmeisteri" subSpecies="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pelidnota burmeisteri tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
